    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>There is no need for a custom inspection, the necessary inspection is built in. Go to\n<code>Setting | Editor | Inspections</code> and enable the inspection\n<code>JVM languages | Test frameworks | Test-only usage in production code</code>. Then a warning will be reported if members with the <code>@VisibleForTesting</code> annotation are accessed from production code, but not from test code.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Note: before IntelliJ 2024.1.7 , the inspection could be found under <code>Java | General | Test-only class or method call in production code</code>.</p>\n"
  } ],
